      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 18.24,
      "end": 21.2,
      "text": "ESOP's Fables, the Dog and the Sow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.48,
      "end": 31.06,
      "text": "A dog and a Sow were arguing, and each claimed that its own young ones were finer than those of any other animal.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 32.02,
      "end": 40.44,
      "text": "Well, said the Sow at last, mine can see at any rate when they come into the world, but yours are born blind.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 42.06,
      "end": 43.98,
      "text": "End of the Dog and the Sow.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
